 ```
 
+#### `contents.setJavaScriptDialogHandler(handler)`
+
+* `handler` Function | null
+  * `details` [JavaScriptDialogHandlerDetails](structures/javascript-dialog-handler-details.md)
+  * `dialog` [AlertJavaScriptDialog](structures/alert-javascript-dialog.md) | [ConfirmJavaScriptDialog](structures/confirm-javascript-dialog.md) | [PromptJavaScriptDialog](structures/prompt-javascript-dialog.md) | [BeforeUnloadJavaScriptDialog](structures/before-unload-javascript-dialog.md)
+
+Sets a handler for renderer-initiated JavaScript dialogs. Passing `null` clears
+the handler and restores Electron's default handling.
+
+The handler receives `alert`, `confirm`, `prompt`, and `beforeunload` dialogs.
+Each dialog object exposes only the methods valid for its `type`. The method
+returns `true` when it handles the dialog, and returns `false` if the dialog was
+already handled or canceled. A dialog method may be called asynchronously after
+the handler returns.
+
+When no handler is set, `alert`, `confirm`, and `prompt` use Electron's built-in
+message box handling, and `beforeunload` continues to use the
+[`will-prevent-unload`](#event-will-prevent-unload) event.
+
+```js
+const { BrowserWindow } = require('electron')
+
+const win = new BrowserWindow()
+
+win.webContents.setJavaScriptDialogHandler(async (details, dialog) => {
+  switch (dialog.type) {
+    case 'alert':
+      dialog.ok()
+      break
+    case 'confirm':
+      dialog.confirm()
+      break
+    case 'prompt':
+      dialog.submit(await getPromptText(details))
+      break
+    case 'beforeunload':
+      dialog.leave()
+      break
+  }
+})
+```
+
